6.09pm Which camp would you want to be right now? South Africa picked eight wickets, but Australia are already ahead by 218 runs. Runs on the board always crucial. Another 14-wicket day: 14 for 239 on day 2, and could have been a lot more. Australia were 73 for 7 at one stage, and looked like going down quickly with the ball wobbling all around. But Carey and Starc put up a defiant stand, 61 for the eighth wicket. And that's given Australia a lot of breathing space. South Africa were excellent all innings. They induced a lot of edges, which didn't carry. Starc also gave a couple of chances, one a fairly easy one in the final over which Jansen failed to hang on to. Lungi Ngidi and Kagiso Rabada picked three wickets apiece while Jansen and Mulder picked a wicket each. How much can Australia stretch their lead tomorrow? Will South Africa chase whatever target they get? Will this Test go into day four? Lots of questions to be answered. Join us nice and early tomorrow as we search for some of the answers. Till then, this is me Ashish Pant, signing off on behalf of Alex, Raghav and Ranjith. Ciao!

Lungi Ngidi: We were still in the game, they bowled very well. At the end of the day, we still had a job to do. The coach asked us, do whatever you do, do it with conviction. Obviously, if you go out, go out on your own terms. [His bowling] The first innings was tough, there was no rhythm. I was fighting a lot while bowling. There were some nerves. Once I got the rhythm I went running with it. [Crowd] It was pretty exciting. Hearing my name, just gave me the energy. [SA's position] We are in a good position. Two balls could wrap it up. We will focus on that. Chasing anything under 250 it won't be easy, but we will want to give ourselves the best chance.

vinay: "Carey is the most underrated player I believe. impact in every match is big. pick any series in last 2/3 years. "

Chamal Perera: "Aussies are a bit ahead right now. Another 30 runs tomorrow morning would make them a lot more comfortable."

kevin: "well, SA can't say they didn't have their chances (or half chances). disappointing end to a fighting day!"
